@strangeLoops do you know the pinecil soldering iron and its OS firmware, the IronOS?
maybe you can get some ideas for your code (and UI) there: https://github.com/Ralim/IronOS
The IronOS also works on the other tiny heatplate that was tested by greatscott

I'm not experience with this language but could this be the cause of the 'hokey' behavior? 

  //Debounce
  while(!digitalRead(upsw) || !digitalRead(dnsw)) {  }

It seems the only way to get through this debounce check is to press both buttons. I also discovered that holding both buttons allows it to heat. I think this While() is preventing that.

> Also, you can i.e. make one side with the PCB, but the over side in the oven, because the PCB won't work with one side full of components.
@spelter
yh, i cannot wait to be able to prototype two-sided boards at home. i'm still waiting for the boards i designed, and components to arrive though.
